pollution in halong bay
Cruised on Halong Bay on Paloma for 1N 2D(overpriced and overated) during May 2010. The water was pretty clean until we went kyaking to a fishing village. It was dificult not to paddle through raw sewage and tissue papers. My wife copped a faceful when she lifted her paddle!! In the evening we fished for squid off the rear of the boat. This is when we saw a large amount of debris pass by the boat which included plastics,raw sewage and tissue paper. (and yes, squid was on the menu the next day!)Halong Bay is a beautiful place but the future does not look good for tourism unless the authorities clamp down on the polluters
