AussieGal23
Perth3 contributions
Pinta Cruiser with Columbus
Ha Long Bay is like the pyramids - a must see but possibly doesn't live up to your expectations. The air pollution was terrible making for a very 'foggy' couple of days - the sky did clear on the last day on the way home... The boat was quite comfortable for the 1 night, although we may as well have been camping the mattresses were so hard. The staff were lovely and the food abundant!! A bit of a problem if you don't like seafood...
Another let-down was the condition of the water in the bay - quite polluted with an thin oil slick across it the whole way.
No matter how careful we were with sanitising our hands at every moment, we both got terrible gastro... I have to question the food hygiene, especially when it came to the seafood and where they obtained their cooking water...
Overall, cool boat, awesome little paddle through some caves on the second day but I won't be rushing back. Would more expensive boats offer a different experience? I'm not sure. I'd only recommend this to a friend with them going in with eyes wide open.
