markllydselby
Cardiff, UK27 contributions
1
Ha Long Bay - Don't Miss It!
Mar 2020
My wife and I were fortunate to have seen Ha Long Bay in a way that not many people are able to. We were in Vietnam at the outbreak of COVID-19 restrictions and the Chinese border closed shortly prior to our visit to Ha Long Bay. Tourist trips to Ha Long Bay had virtually stopped by that point and we were on one of only two (possibly 3) tour boats that were still operating. At one point I appeared to be the only person swimming in the entire bay. There's probably little that I can add by way of description to that which others haven't already said so I'll limit myself to some tips
1. This is a truly remarkable place and you should definitely make every effort to see it
2. Don't feel that an overnight stay is essential. We booked a one day excursion from Hanoi and we had a wonderful time
3. Don't forget your swimwear. It's very easy to get changed on the tour boats
4. Unless you're physically unable make the effort to visit the cave. The steps aren't as challenging as they appear and there are stages where you can rest and catch your breath
